    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle and peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick)\u00a0over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, tear your <strong>'Nduja </strong>into the pan<strong> </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>with a generous grind of\u00a0<strong>black pepper</strong>\u00a0and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the 'Nduja is softening, add\u00a0your <strong>quick cook spaghetti</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a pot of\u00a0<strong>boiled water</strong>\u00a0with\u00a0a generous pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook\u00a0for\u00a02-3 min or until the spaghetti and Tenderstem broccoli are cooked with a slight bite, then drain, reserving a cup of the\u00a0<strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the pot with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the 'Nduja has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> stock mix </strong>with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate your <strong>egg yolk[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>from the <strong>whites </strong>by cracking your<strong> egg[s] </strong>over a small bowl and catching the <strong>yolk</strong> in the shell</p><p>Transfer the<strong> yolk </strong>from one shell half to the other several times, until all the<strong> whites </strong>are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell</p><p>Tip: Hold on to those egg whites! They're perfect for meringues or a protein-rich omelette (they freeze well too)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> in a jug with your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>carbonara sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the pan from the heat and add the\u00a0<strong>drained spaghetti</strong> <strong>& Tenderstem broccoli</strong></p><p>Add\u00a0the\u00a0<strong>carbonara sauce</strong> with a splash of\u00a0<strong>reserved</strong> <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and the <strong>spinach </strong>and mix until fully combined \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>spicy 'Nduja spaghetti carbonara</strong></p><p>Tip: Mix the sauce through the pasta quickly to avoid scrambling the egg!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-spaghetti-carbonara/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the spicy<strong> 'Nduja spaghetti carbonara</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
